definition.value: A member of the class of 6-aminopurines that is  adenine carrying a (furan-2-ylmethyl) substituent at the exocyclic amino group.
Any N-acetyl-D-glucosaminide having alpha-configuration at the anomeric centre.
A tolualdehyde compound with the methyl substituent at the 2-position.
An aminobenzoic acid that is anthranilic acid in which the hydrogen at position 3 is substituted by a methoxy group. It is a metabolite of kynurenine.
A D-fucopyranose with a beta-configuration at the anomeric position.
A penicillin compound having a 6beta-(phenoxyacetyl)amino side-chain.
An epoxycarotenol derivative of lutein.
An N-glycoloylglucosamine of D configuration.
A ketoaldonic acid that is D-gluconic acid in which the hydroxy group at position 2 has been oxidised to a keto group.

An N-acyl-amino acid that is a form of the water-soluble vitamin B9. Its biologically active forms (tetrahydrofolate and others) are essential for nucleotide biosynthesis and homocysteine remethylation.
A D-ribopyranose with a beta-configuration at the anomeric position.
The D-enantiomer of valine.
A D-mannosamine in open-chain aldehydo-form.

Cinchonan in which a hydrogen at position 9 is substituted by hydroxy (S configuration). It occurs in the bark of most varieties of Cinchona shrubs, and is frequently used for directing chirality in asymmetric synthesis.
A hydroxycoumarin that is coumarin substituted by a hydroxy group ay position 7.
A glycosylglucose in which the glycosyl moiety is L-rhamnose linked alpha to C-6 of D-glucose.
Any L-cysteine derivative obtained by conversion of the thiol group into a sulfide.
Any mannoside in which the anomeric centre has alpha-configuration.
A member of the class of leukotrienes that is leukotriene B4 in which the terminal methyl group has undergone formal oxidation to the corresponding carboxylic acid.
An aminobenzoic acid that is salicylic acid substituted by an amino group at position 4.
A polysaccharide composed of repeating units of arabinosylgalactose.
An alpha-amino acid that is propanoic acid bearing an amino substituent at position 2 and a 1H-imidazol-4-yl group at position 3.
A keto-disaccharide that is beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-beta-D-glucose in which the hydroxy group at position 3 of the galactosyl moiety has been oxidised to the corresponding ketone.
The beta-anomer of L-rhamnopyranose.
A poly(glycerol phosphate) macromolecule having alpha-D-glucosyl residues at the secondary hydroxy groups on the repeating units.
The D-enantiomer of psicose.
A hydrate that is the trihydrate form of dipotassium bis[mu-tartrato(4-)]diantimonate(2-).

A spiroketal, monensin A is the major component of monensin, a mixture of antibiotic substances produced by Streptomyces cinnamonensis. An antiprotozoal, it is used as the sodium salt as a feed additive for the prevention of coccidiosis in poultry and as a growth promoter in cattle.
